I egenskap av entreprenörer, pedagoger och forskare möts vi, för att tackla de största pedagogiska utmaningarna såsom de som är i verksamheten lyfter fram dem. Vi omvandlar konkreta problem till möjligheter och söker innovativa lösningar tillsammans.

Krav på kunskap, ambition och förmåga

Denna grupp är inget snackforum. För att gå med och delta i gruppen ska du besitta kunskap, ambition och förmåga att förändra skolan.

Varför skapar vi denna mötesplats?

• Fröken Ann, förstelärare Glömstaskolan, initiativtagare till #skolvåren: Jag vill bidra till behovsbaserad innovation och utveckling av skolan. 

• Martin Tiberg, grundare av Invigos, projektledare Alla kan skriva: Jag förväntar mig nya insikter, livliga diskussioner och formering av nya lag av passionerade människor som bygger framtidens pedagogik.

•Magister Magnus Blixt, lärare, författare, föreläsare mm: Jag förväntar mig tankespjärn och konkret arbete för att inte bara prata om behov och problem, utan också att vi tar konkreta steg mot fungerande lösningar.

category.name: education/learning
description:
Are you the curious type like us who want to discover, understand and apply personality profiling in order to improve yourself? To understand others? Do you have a general fascination for human behaviour? Then you have come to the right place.

Trough a series of meetings and discussions this group aims to help other members to understand and grow.

To do that, we focuses on the following school of thoughts:

Jung, MBTI, Socionics, Keirsey, Social Styles, DISC, Strengths Finder and Big Five. Probably more along the way, but lets start with those.

Some key areas we explore are:

• How we see the world
• How we make decisions
• How we represent ourselves to others
• What our key strengths and weaknesses are

The group has three primary types of meetings:

I - Introduction meetings: Experienced members share their knowledge. Mainly aimed at beginners.

D - Discussion meetings: Meetings aimed at getting together and discussion or performing activities, or both

L – Lecture meetings: External guests or prominent members. These could potentially include costs for venue or presenter, or both.

Sounds good? We strive to improve continuously and hope you want to join us during our quest for knowledge.

All the best, 
Pierre, Elif, Anton, Karolina, Christopher and Parham

PS. If you haven't done any personality test yet, and would like to find out. Please take this free test to find out, and come back and join us. 

http://www.celebritytypes.com/test.php
name: Personaire - Making sense of the inside noise

category.name: education/learning
description:
This is a group about self improvement through science, especially psychology, and applied math. Our ideal members are people who want to be their best selves and are willing to put in a little work to achieve that. You should be willing to do back-of-the-envelope calculations and change your mind when you receive a convincing argument.

You should join because you'll learn useful things and meet level-headed friends. You can expect talks and workshops every week or two, where one person will present material, followed by an informal discussion. Typical topics include decision theory applied to everyday life, cognitive biases to watch out for, techniques for achieving goals, and the latest research on health and nutrition. Looking forward to swapping tips and clear-headed debate with everybody!

description:
Hello,


This is a group for those interested in cosmology and the philosophy of cosmology as an interdisciplinary discipline that encompasses science, politics, philosophy and well-belonging. We lack a shared cosmology in this scattered world. Cosmological-science highly speculative insights can be inspiration for a better life on earth.This group was created by Luis de Miranda, philosophical practitioner in Stockholm and director of the Philosophical Parlour: http://luisdemiranda.com

Luis has proposed a shared cosmology based on the concept of Creal. Read more here: https://crealectics.com

And here: On the Concept of Creal: The Politico-Ethical Horizon of a Creative Absolute: https://philpapers.org/rec/DEMOTC-3

description:
For anyone wanting or having delved into Nietzschean philosophy. The meetup will be co-created between us participants. The current proposed structure is to form small groups and choose a section from any of his books, then interpret and discuss that section to grow our understanding of his ideas. I'm currently reading beyond good and evil.

Location: Stockholm Public Library

Maybe you have gotten stuck on a section or you can't wrap your head around a quote. Maybe you just can't get enough of Nietzsche and want to learn from others interpretations. Either way, bring your inner torch, your favorite books and quotes, come join us and let's explore the depths of Nietzschean philosophy!

category.name: education/learning
description:
Digital Marketing Workshops are perfect if you are a small business owner, an entrepreneur, a student looking for career options, a startup, or a person interested in the digital. 

The workshops take the DIY approach, teach you how to manage everything yourself and how to gain the digital mindset. It is a hands-on workshop which means that you will really be making, designing and working on your projects and having the final product after each workshop.

The workshops are held in English.

WHAT? 

Each workshop will cover one of the topics:

– Logo: colour, shape and apps that make logos,

– Photography: mobile phone photography and post-production, preparing your pictures for the web,

– Social networks: opening accounts, managing, designing and maintaining,

– Content creation: writing for the web, incorporating pictures and videos, posting and paid advertising,

– Community management: how to communicate and connect with your audience,

– SEO and Google: writing for Google – how to be likeable by Google,

– AdWords: advertising on Google,

– WordPress website: how to build your site or blog from scratch.

WHEN?

Every Wednesday from 18:00 to 20:00.

WHERE?

Uppsala, Sweden, Hera Hub: https://herahub.com/sweden/

INSTRUCTOR?

Ivana Marinković: http://superbravo.design/contact/

HOW MUCH?

SEK 650 per workshop for non-members of Hera Hub.

SEK 520 per workshop for the members of Hera Hub.

HOW TO SIGN UP?

Please RSVP and make the payment (betala till bg 5216-7699) before the workshop.

WHY?

Because it improves business and boosts up ideas. Because it opens new possibilities of reaching out to customers. Because it upgrades the quality of your services. Because the digital approach to business is inevitable today. Because brings new perspectives. Because it's fun!

HAVE ANY QUESTIONS?

Please write a comment or on email@superbravo.design.

See you soon!

We dream of living in a world where the life lottery is fair and everybody has what they feel is a fair chance at a good life. 

We meet one Friday a month to talk and discuss. We'll be up to 5 people at each meetup.  Bring your lunch with you! Please suggest topics that you'd like to discuss, and join on the days that we discuss topics that interest you!

Topics we've discussed:

• principles and values for teams and companies

• complexity theory

• democracy vs leadership

• reducing our climate footprint

•Magister Magnus Blixt, lärare, författare, föreläsare mm: Jag förväntar mig tankespjärn och konkret arbete för att inte bara prata om behov och problem, utan också att vi tar konkreta steg mot fungerande lösningar.

description:
Are you the curious type like us who want to discover, understand and apply personality profiling in order to improve yourself? To understand others? Do you have a general fascination for human behaviour? Then you have come to the right place.

Trough a series of meetings and discussions this group aims to help other members to understand and grow.

To do that, we focuses on the following school of thoughts:

Jung, MBTI, Socionics, Keirsey, Social Styles, DISC, Strengths Finder and Big Five. Probably more along the way, but lets start with those.

Some key areas we explore are:

• How we see the world
• How we make decisions
• How we represent ourselves to others
• What our key strengths and weaknesses are

The group has three primary types of meetings:

I - Introduction meetings: Experienced members share their knowledge. Mainly aimed at beginners.

D - Discussion meetings: Meetings aimed at getting together and discussion or performing activities, or both

L – Lecture meetings: External guests or prominent members. These could potentially include costs for venue or presenter, or both.

Sounds good? We strive to improve continuously and hope you want to join us during our quest for knowledge.

All the best, 
Pierre, Elif, Anton, Karolina, Christopher and Parham

PS. If you haven't done any personality test yet, and would like to find out. Please take this free test to find out, and come back and join us. 

http://www.celebritytypes.com/test.php
name: Personaire - Making sense of the inside noise

description:
This is a group about self improvement through science, especially psychology, and applied math. Our ideal members are people who want to be their best selves and are willing to put in a little work to achieve that. You should be willing to do back-of-the-envelope calculations and change your mind when you receive a convincing argument.

You should join because you'll learn useful things and meet level-headed friends. You can expect talks and workshops every week or two, where one person will present material, followed by an informal discussion. Typical topics include decision theory applied to everyday life, cognitive biases to watch out for, techniques for achieving goals, and the latest research on health and nutrition. Looking forward to swapping tips and clear-headed debate with everybody!

Är du matintresserad och nyfiken på att höra om och smaka på nya innovativa produkter? Vill du lära dig mer om de senaste vetenskapliga insikterna och om socialt arbete kring mat och livsmedel? description:
Hello,


This is a group for those interested in cosmology and the philosophy of cosmology as an interdisciplinary discipline that encompasses science, politics, philosophy and well-belonging. We lack a shared cosmology in this scattered world. Cosmological-science highly speculative insights can be inspiration for a better life on earth.This group was created by Luis de Miranda, philosophical practitioner in Stockholm and director of the Philosophical Parlour: http://luisdemiranda.com

Luis has proposed a shared cosmology based on the concept of Creal. Read more here: https://crealectics.com

And here: On the Concept of Creal: The Politico-Ethical Horizon of a Creative Absolute: https://philpapers.org/rec/DEMOTC-3
name: Developing a Shared Cosmology

description:
For anyone wanting or having delved into Nietzschean philosophy. The meetup will be co-created between us participants. The current proposed structure is to form small groups and choose a section from any of his books, then interpret and discuss that section to grow our understanding of his ideas. I'm currently reading beyond good and evil.

Location: Stockholm Public Library

Maybe you have gotten stuck on a section or you can't wrap your head around a quote. Maybe you just can't get enough of Nietzsche and want to learn from others interpretations. Either way, bring your inner torch, your favorite books and quotes, come join us and let's explore the depths of Nietzschean philosophy!

category.name: education/learning
description:
Digital Marketing Workshops are perfect if you are a small business owner, an entrepreneur, a student looking for career options, a startup, or a person interested in the digital. 

The workshops take the DIY approach, teach you how to manage everything yourself and how to gain the digital mindset. It is a hands-on workshop which means that you will really be making, designing and working on your projects and having the final product after each workshop.

The workshops are held in English.

WHAT? 

Each workshop will cover one of the topics:

– Logo: colour, shape and apps that make logos,

– Photography: mobile phone photography and post-production, preparing your pictures for the web,

– Social networks: opening accounts, managing, designing and maintaining,

– Content creation: writing for the web, incorporating pictures and videos, posting and paid advertising,

– Community management: how to communicate and connect with your audience,

– SEO and Google: writing for Google – how to be likeable by Google,

– AdWords: advertising on Google,

– WordPress website: how to build your site or blog from scratch.

WHEN?

Every Wednesday from 18:00 to 20:00.

WHERE?

Uppsala, Sweden, Hera Hub: https://herahub.com/sweden/

INSTRUCTOR?

Ivana Marinković: http://superbravo.design/contact/

HOW MUCH?

SEK 650 per workshop for non-members of Hera Hub.

SEK 520 per workshop for the members of Hera Hub.

HOW TO SIGN UP?

Please RSVP and make the payment (betala till bg 5216-7699) before the workshop.

WHY?

Because it improves business and boosts up ideas. Because it opens new possibilities of reaching out to customers. Because it upgrades the quality of your services. Because the digital approach to business is inevitable today. Because brings new perspectives. Because it's fun!

HAVE ANY QUESTIONS?

Please write a comment or on email@superbravo.design.

See you soon!

description:
We believe that all people are equal and that they are inherently good. We listen to learn. We want our hypotheses to be challenged. We're here to learn and challenge, but not to convert. If this describes you too, then this is your room for discussing the things that are important to you.

We dream of living in a world where the life lottery is fair and everybody has what they feel is a fair chance at a good life. 

We meet one Friday a month to talk and discuss. We'll be up to 5 people at each meetup.  Bring your lunch with you! Please suggest topics that you'd like to discuss, and join on the days that we discuss topics that interest you!

Topics we've discussed:

• principles and values for teams and companies

• complexity theory

• democracy vs leadership

• reducing our climate footprint

Krav på kunskap, ambition och förmåga

Denna grupp är inget snackforum. För att gå med och delta i gruppen ska du besitta kunskap, ambition och förmåga att förändra skolan.

Varför skapar vi denna mötesplats?

• Fröken Ann, förstelärare Glömstaskolan, initiativtagare till #skolvåren: Jag vill bidra till behovsbaserad innovation och utveckling av skolan. 

• Martin Tiberg, grundare av Invigos, projektledare Alla kan skriva: Jag förväntar mig nya insikter, livliga diskussioner och formering av nya lag av passionerade människor som bygger framtidens pedagogik.

•Magister Magnus Blixt, lärare, författare, föreläsare mm: Jag förväntar mig tankespjärn och konkret arbete för att inte bara prata om behov och problem, utan också att vi tar konkreta steg mot fungerande lösningar.

category.name: education/learning
description:
Are you the curious type like us who want to discover, understand and apply personality profiling in order to improve yourself? To understand others? Do you have a general fascination for human behaviour? Then you have come to the right place.

Trough a series of meetings and discussions this group aims to help other members to understand and grow.

To do that, we focuses on the following school of thoughts:

Jung, MBTI, Socionics, Keirsey, Social Styles, DISC, Strengths Finder and Big Five. Probably more along the way, but lets start with those.

Some key areas we explore are:

• How we see the world
• How we make decisions
• How we represent ourselves to others
• What our key strengths and weaknesses are

The group has three primary types of meetings:

I - Introduction meetings: Experienced members share their knowledge. Mainly aimed at beginners.

D - Discussion meetings: Meetings aimed at getting together and discussion or performing activities, or both

L – Lecture meetings: External guests or prominent members. These could potentially include costs for venue or presenter, or both.

Sounds good? We strive to improve continuously and hope you want to join us during our quest for knowledge.

All the best, 
Pierre, Elif, Anton, Karolina, Christopher and Parham

PS. If you haven't done any personality test yet, and would like to find out. Please take this free test to find out, and come back and join us. 

http://www.celebritytypes.com/test.php
name: Personaire - Making sense of the inside noise

description:
This is a group about self improvement through science, especially psychology, and applied math. Our ideal members are people who want to be their best selves and are willing to put in a little work to achieve that. You should be willing to do back-of-the-envelope calculations and change your mind when you receive a convincing argument.

You should join because you'll learn useful things and meet level-headed friends. You can expect talks and workshops every week or two, where one person will present material, followed by an informal discussion. Typical topics include decision theory applied to everyday life, cognitive biases to watch out for, techniques for achieving goals, and the latest research on health and nutrition. Looking forward to swapping tips and clear-headed debate with everybody!
name: Stockholm Lesswrong

description:
Hello,


This is a group for those interested in cosmology and the philosophy of cosmology as an interdisciplinary discipline that encompasses science, politics, philosophy and well-belonging. We lack a shared cosmology in this scattered world. Cosmological-science highly speculative insights can be inspiration for a better life on earth.This group was created by Luis de Miranda, philosophical practitioner in Stockholm and director of the Philosophical Parlour: http://luisdemiranda.com

Luis has proposed a shared cosmology based on the concept of Creal. Read more here: https://crealectics.com

And here: On the Concept of Creal: The Politico-Ethical Horizon of a Creative Absolute: https://philpapers.org/rec/DEMOTC-3

category.name: education/learning
description:
Digital Marketing Workshops are perfect if you are a small business owner, an entrepreneur, a student looking for career options, a startup, or a person interested in the digital. 

The workshops take the DIY approach, teach you how to manage everything yourself and how to gain the digital mindset. It is a hands-on workshop which means that you will really be making, designing and working on your projects and having the final product after each workshop.

The workshops are held in English.

WHAT? 

Each workshop will cover one of the topics:

– Logo: colour, shape and apps that make logos,

– Photography: mobile phone photography and post-production, preparing your pictures for the web,

– Social networks: opening accounts, managing, designing and maintaining,

– Content creation: writing for the web, incorporating pictures and videos, posting and paid advertising,

– Community management: how to communicate and connect with your audience,

– SEO and Google: writing for Google – how to be likeable by Google,

– AdWords: advertising on Google,

– WordPress website: how to build your site or blog from scratch.

WHEN?

Every Wednesday from 18:00 to 20:00.

WHERE?

category.name: education/learning
description:
What really motivates you? What makes you get up in the morning and do what you do? In this group we discuss, compare and evaluate different motivational frameworks with special focus on Reiss Motivation Profile.

The motivational research by the American Professor Steven Reiss forms the scientific basis of the Reiss Motivation Profile. Using numerous studies with thousands of trial subjects he identified a total of 16 psychological basic desires which every human being possesses. These basic desires must be satisfied in order that we feel our lives to be meaningful. They are moulded by our genes and experiences in childhood and adolescence, remain largely constant throughout our lives in accordance with previous perceptions and thus give us permanent orientation. As with every other scientific procedure in personality or motivational psychology, you have to decide entirely as an individual which indicators from the results are important or meaningful for you – and which not. The following questions may help you: How well does each basic desire characteristic describe my actual need? At which places do the statements apply particularly well, and in which points do I not recognise myself? How do I live each basic desire in my day-to-day life? These are questions that all people should be able to answer to be able to fill their lives with Value based happiness.

If you are interested in living your life (and worklife) with greater fulfillment and joy, join us in the discussion at the next meetup.

description:
Jag heter Anna Jelen och bor för det mesta i Schweiz eller reser omkring med mitt företag. Man kallar mig för "The Time Expert" - jag är key note speaker, workshop ledare och ämnet är enkelt: det är om tiden vi har. :-)

My name is Anna Jelen and I am also called the time expert. I am a coach, a mentor, a time management entrepreneur, key note speaker and the producer of the „Have a good day“ program (which will be in English summer 2017). Others also call me a Life Strategist. 


I can give advice and practical tips and tricks on: 

- how to improve your time management 

- how to improve your stress management 

- how to be happy and live a good life 

- good time management exercises 

- ideas for your personal development plan / skills 

- tipps for your work life balance 

- time management for students, adults, kids, actually for everyone - even time management for dummies 😃 


I keep on saying: we should not just use time management methods, rather live a good time management. Good time management should be a life philosophy, a life style, not just methods and concepts. Time management goes hand in hand with personal development - that’s what good time management is about. 


I will give you hints and advices in a simpel funny weekly vlog for your daily life. Let’s also talk about: ofttimes, digital detox, how to be productive and efficient, learn to focus and let’s discuss determination and what that is all about. 


Never forget: you need a good stress and time management for your personal development, to have a good life, to have good relationships, for personal growth - simply: to have a good and happy life. 


I will give you funny, inspirational and motivational speeches (or vlogs). 


Subscribe to my YouTube channel if you like it. That would be great! 


You can also find me here: 

Annas Homepage (soon in English) : https://anna-jelen.com/updates/

Annas products (soon in English) : www.TheTimeExpert.ch The program is about How to have a good day - enjoy! 


Instagram: 

https://www.instagram.com/annaathetim...


Facebook: 

https://www.facebook.com/jelenseminare/


LinkedIn: 

https://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-jele...


Xing: 

https://www.xing.com/profile/Anna_Jel...


I can't wait to meet you guys and talk about time! 

Hej! 

Jag bor i Schweiz och är kallad The Time Expert - för det är det jag gör: jag pratar om tiden och hur vi går igenom livet utan stress och ändå kan avancera med planerna man har. Hur man kan leva livet man vill ha. Hur man inte stressar ihjäl sig om vardagen. Hur vi kan lära oss att ha en bra balans i livet. För tiden är allt vi har. 
Gärna skulle jag träffa dig denna kvällen för att berätta för dig om olika upplevelser jag har haft angående "tiden". Det ska motivera dig att leva livet du vill "egentligen" leva. är du med? Kom - Stockholm 7th of october !

category.name: education/learning
description:
Sokratiska panelsamtal går till såhär. Man tar en personlig berättelse och lirkar därifrån ut allmängiltiga principer. En berättar, ett par hjälper till att förtydliga och förallmängiltiga, och en antecknar. Publiken gör invändningar; antecknaren drar pilar och blandar engelska och svenska hysteriskt på whiteboarden. Principerna man nått fram till torde vara samma oavsett avstampsberättelse. (Teoretiskt sett. Och med lite övning.) Målet är att få några förklarande definitioner av mångbottnade begrepp, t.ex. ”praktisk visdom”. Målet är att få med sig principer att applicera nästa gång man är i en situation som efterfrågar det.

Socratic Panel Discussions go like this. We start with a personal story and move from there to universal principles. One person on the panel tells a story and the others help look for clarity and universality through questioning. The audience contributes, adding ideas and concepts to the discussion, which is a mix of English and Swedish. Throughout the discussion someone takes notes on a whiteboard, capturing the movement and key points. The aim is to reach toward universally applicable principles; for example, a multifaceted definition of the concept 'practical wisdom'. The thought is that the new and deeper understanding we gain of these concepts can be directly applied the next time we face similar situations.

En meet up för alla som vill utforska och byta erfarenheter kring Sociocracy 3.0 – ett princip och mönsterbaserat förhållningssätt för att skapa effektiva samarbeten i organisationer på olika nivåer. Vi diskuterar förslagsbaserade förbättringar, bifallsbaserade beslutsmodeller, cirklar, organisatorisk agilitet och mycket mer. <br>

Vi träffas i Göteborg med roterande träffpunkter – initial puls en gång per kvartal!

Välkomna!

Bodil A + Bea D

Radical Collaboration driver:

”We work with & coach individuals and teams working in small and large organisations.

We need a Sociocracy 3.0  network in Gothenburg  to secure exchange of inspiration, insights, practices and experience that will strengthen us in our work to support individuals & teams within the organisations we are serving.”

This meet up will strive to organize content sharing with:
- Lightning talks
- S3 pattern simulations
- S3 principles and patterns useful in everyday work and life that can make a difference in making Gothenburg a better place to live in
- Challenges to continue to discuss/bring home between meetups
- Combine when needed open space, sub groups and whole group exchanges

This meetup will strive to organize sessions in the following manner:
- Breakfast meet ups (ca 07.30-10.00)
- Rotating time and hosts
- Meet every 5th week/bimonthly
- Evaluate in June 2018 towards the meet up driver

Evaluation criteria:
- increase of meet up members daring to try one or several S3 patterns
- increase of amount of people daring to broaden their use of S3 patterns in organisations they work in

category.name: education/learning
description:
What really motivates you? What makes you get up in the morning and do what you do? In this group we discuss, compare and evaluate different motivational frameworks with special focus on Reiss Motivation Profile.

The motivational research by the American Professor Steven Reiss forms the scientific basis of the Reiss Motivation Profile. Using numerous studies with thousands of trial subjects he identified a total of 16 psychological basic desires which every human being possesses. These basic desires must be satisfied in order that we feel our lives to be meaningful. They are moulded by our genes and experiences in childhood and adolescence, remain largely constant throughout our lives in accordance with previous perceptions and thus give us permanent orientation. As with every other scientific procedure in personality or motivational psychology, you have to decide entirely as an individual which indicators from the results are important or meaningful for you – and which not. The following questions may help you: How well does each basic desire characteristic describe my actual need? At which places do the statements apply particularly well, and in which points do I not recognise myself? How do I live each basic desire in my day-to-day life? These are questions that all people should be able to answer to be able to fill their lives with Value based happiness.

If you are interested in living your life (and worklife) with greater fulfillment and joy, join us in the discussion at the next meetup.
name: Motivation in life and business - Göteborg

description:
Jag heter Anna Jelen och bor för det mesta i Schweiz eller reser omkring med mitt företag. Man kallar mig för "The Time Expert" - jag är key note speaker, workshop ledare och ämnet är enkelt: det är om tiden vi har. :-)

My name is Anna Jelen and I am also called the time expert. I am a coach, a mentor, a time management entrepreneur, key note speaker and the producer of the „Have a good day“ program (which will be in English summer 2017). Others also call me a Life Strategist. 


I can give advice and practical tips and tricks on: 

- how to improve your time management 

- how to improve your stress management 

- how to be happy and live a good life 

- good time management exercises 

- ideas for your personal development plan / skills 

- tipps for your work life balance 

- time management for students, adults, kids, actually for everyone - even time management for dummies 😃 


I keep on saying: we should not just use time management methods, rather live a good time management. Good time management should be a life philosophy, a life style, not just methods and concepts. Time management goes hand in hand with personal development - that’s what good time management is about. 


I will give you hints and advices in a simpel funny weekly vlog for your daily life. Let’s also talk about: ofttimes, digital detox, how to be productive and efficient, learn to focus and let’s discuss determination and what that is all about. 


Never forget: you need a good stress and time management for your personal development, to have a good life, to have good relationships, for personal growth - simply: to have a good and happy life. 


I will give you funny, inspirational and motivational speeches (or vlogs). 


Subscribe to my YouTube channel if you like it. That would be great! 


You can also find me here: 

Annas Homepage (soon in English) : https://anna-jelen.com/updates/

Annas products (soon in English) : www.TheTimeExpert.ch The program is about How to have a good day - enjoy! 


Instagram: 

https://www.instagram.com/annaathetim...


Facebook: 

https://www.facebook.com/jelenseminare/


LinkedIn: 

https://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-jele...


Xing: 

https://www.xing.com/profile/Anna_Jel...


I can't wait to meet you guys and talk about time! 

Hej! 

Jag bor i Schweiz och är kallad The Time Expert - för det är det jag gör: jag pratar om tiden och hur vi går igenom livet utan stress och ändå kan avancera med planerna man har. Hur man kan leva livet man vill ha. Hur man inte stressar ihjäl sig om vardagen. Hur vi kan lära oss att ha en bra balans i livet. För tiden är allt vi har. 
Gärna skulle jag träffa dig denna kvällen för att berätta för dig om olika upplevelser jag har haft angående "tiden". Det ska motivera dig att leva livet du vill "egentligen" leva. är du med? Kom - Stockholm 7th of october !

category.name: education/learning
description:
Sokratiska panelsamtal går till såhär. Man tar en personlig berättelse och lirkar därifrån ut allmängiltiga principer. En berättar, ett par hjälper till att förtydliga och förallmängiltiga, och en antecknar. Publiken gör invändningar; antecknaren drar pilar och blandar engelska och svenska hysteriskt på whiteboarden. Principerna man nått fram till torde vara samma oavsett avstampsberättelse. (Teoretiskt sett. Och med lite övning.) Målet är att få några förklarande definitioner av mångbottnade begrepp, t.ex. ”praktisk visdom”. Målet är att få med sig principer att applicera nästa gång man är i en situation som efterfrågar det.

Socratic Panel Discussions go like this. We start with a personal story and move from there to universal principles. One person on the panel tells a story and the others help look for clarity and universality through questioning. The audience contributes, adding ideas and concepts to the discussion, which is a mix of English and Swedish. Throughout the discussion someone takes notes on a whiteboard, capturing the movement and key points. The aim is to reach toward universally applicable principles; for example, a multifaceted definition of the concept 'practical wisdom'. The thought is that the new and deeper understanding we gain of these concepts can be directly applied the next time we face similar situations.

category.name: education/learning
description:
En meet up för alla som vill utforska och byta erfarenheter kring Sociocracy 3.0 – ett princip och mönsterbaserat förhållningssätt för att skapa effektiva samarbeten i organisationer på olika nivåer. Vi diskuterar förslagsbaserade förbättringar, bifallsbaserade beslutsmodeller, cirklar, organisatorisk agilitet och mycket mer. <br>

Vi träffas i Göteborg med roterande träffpunkter – initial puls en gång per kvartal!

Välkomna!

Bodil A + Bea D

Radical Collaboration driver:

”We work with & coach individuals and teams working in small and large organisations.

We need a Sociocracy 3.0  network in Gothenburg  to secure exchange of inspiration, insights, practices and experience that will strengthen us in our work to support individuals & teams within the organisations we are serving.”

This meet up will strive to organize content sharing with:
- Lightning talks
- S3 pattern simulations
- S3 principles and patterns useful in everyday work and life that can make a difference in making Gothenburg a better place to live in
- Challenges to continue to discuss/bring home between meetups
- Combine when needed open space, sub groups and whole group exchanges

This meetup will strive to organize sessions in the following manner:
- Breakfast meet ups (ca 07.30-10.00)
- Rotating time and hosts
- Meet every 5th week/bimonthly
- Evaluate in June 2018 towards the meet up driver

Evaluation criteria:
- increase of meet up members daring to try one or several S3 patterns
- increase of amount of people daring to broaden their use of S3 patterns in organisations they work in

Om du svarade ja på någon av ovanstående frågor säger det egentligen ingenting men vill du träffa andra grubblare med intressen inom filosofi, psykologi, astronomi eller andra ämnen där vi tillsammans kan gräva efter förståelse är du hjärtligt välkommen in i värmen!
name: Amatörfilosofer

•Magister Magnus Blixt, lärare, författare, föreläsare mm: Jag förväntar mig tankespjärn och konkret arbete för att inte bara prata om behov och problem, utan också att vi tar konkreta steg mot fungerande lösningar.

category.name: education/learning
description:
Are you the curious type like us who want to discover, understand and apply personality profiling in order to improve yourself? To understand others? Do you have a general fascination for human behaviour? Then you have come to the right place.

Trough a series of meetings and discussions this group aims to help other members to understand and grow.

To do that, we focuses on the following school of thoughts:

Jung, MBTI, Socionics, Keirsey, Social Styles, DISC, Strengths Finder and Big Five. Probably more along the way, but lets start with those.

Some key areas we explore are:

• How we see the world
• How we make decisions
• How we represent ourselves to others
• What our key strengths and weaknesses are

The group has three primary types of meetings:

I - Introduction meetings: Experienced members share their knowledge. Mainly aimed at beginners.

D - Discussion meetings: Meetings aimed at getting together and discussion or performing activities, or both

L – Lecture meetings: External guests or prominent members. These could potentially include costs for venue or presenter, or both.

Sounds good? We strive to improve continuously and hope you want to join us during our quest for knowledge.

All the best, 
Pierre, Elif, Anton, Karolina, Christopher and Parham

PS. If you haven't done any personality test yet, and would like to find out. Please take this free test to find out, and come back and join us. 

http://www.celebritytypes.com/test.php
name: Personaire - Making sense of the inside noise

description:
This is a group about self improvement through science, especially psychology, and applied math. Our ideal members are people who want to be their best selves and are willing to put in a little work to achieve that. You should be willing to do back-of-the-envelope calculations and change your mind when you receive a convincing argument.

You should join because you'll learn useful things and meet level-headed friends. You can expect talks and workshops every week or two, where one person will present material, followed by an informal discussion. Typical topics include decision theory applied to everyday life, cognitive biases to watch out for, techniques for achieving goals, and the latest research on health and nutrition. Looking forward to swapping tips and clear-headed debate with everybody!

description:
Hello,


This is a group for those interested in cosmology and the philosophy of cosmology as an interdisciplinary discipline that encompasses science, politics, philosophy and well-belonging. We lack a shared cosmology in this scattered world. Cosmological-science highly speculative insights can be inspiration for a better life on earth.This group was created by Luis de Miranda, philosophical practitioner in Stockholm and director of the Philosophical Parlour: http://luisdemiranda.com

Luis has proposed a shared cosmology based on the concept of Creal. Read more here: https://crealectics.com

And here: On the Concept of Creal: The Politico-Ethical Horizon of a Creative Absolute: https://philpapers.org/rec/DEMOTC-3

description:
For anyone wanting or having delved into Nietzschean philosophy. The meetup will be co-created between us participants. The current proposed structure is to form small groups and choose a section from any of his books, then interpret and discuss that section to grow our understanding of his ideas. I'm currently reading beyond good and evil.

Location: Stockholm Public Library

Maybe you have gotten stuck on a section or you can't wrap your head around a quote. Maybe you just can't get enough of Nietzsche and want to learn from others interpretations. Either way, bring your inner torch, your favorite books and quotes, come join us and let's explore the depths of Nietzschean philosophy!

description:
We believe that all people are equal and that they are inherently good. We listen to learn. We want our hypotheses to be challenged. We're here to learn and challenge, but not to convert. If this describes you too, then this is your room for discussing the things that are important to you.

We dream of living in a world where the life lottery is fair and everybody has what they feel is a fair chance at a good life. 

We meet one Friday a month to talk and discuss. We'll be up to 5 people at each meetup.  Bring your lunch with you! Please suggest topics that you'd like to discuss, and join on the days that we discuss topics that interest you!

Topics we've discussed:

• principles and values for teams and companies

• complexity theory

• democracy vs leadership

• reducing our climate footprint
name: Exploring the Human Potential for Greater Good

I egenskap av entreprenörer, pedagoger och forskare möts vi, för att tackla de största pedagogiska utmaningarna såsom de som är i verksamheten lyfter fram dem. Vi omvandlar konkreta problem till möjligheter och söker innovativa lösningar tillsammans.

Krav på kunskap, ambition och förmåga

Denna grupp är inget snackforum. För att gå med och delta i gruppen ska du besitta kunskap, ambition och förmåga att förändra skolan.

Varför skapar vi denna mötesplats?

• Fröken Ann, förstelärare Glömstaskolan, initiativtagare till #skolvåren: Jag vill bidra till behovsbaserad innovation och utveckling av skolan. 

• Martin Tiberg, grundare av Invigos, projektledare Alla kan skriva: Jag förväntar mig nya insikter, livliga diskussioner och formering av nya lag av passionerade människor som bygger framtidens pedagogik.

•Magister Magnus Blixt, lärare, författare, föreläsare mm: Jag förväntar mig tankespjärn och konkret arbete för att inte bara prata om behov och problem, utan också att vi tar konkreta steg mot fungerande lösningar.

category.name: education/learning
description:
Are you the curious type like us who want to discover, understand and apply personality profiling in order to improve yourself? To understand others? Do you have a general fascination for human behaviour? Then you have come to the right place.

Trough a series of meetings and discussions this group aims to help other members to understand and grow.

To do that, we focuses on the following school of thoughts:

Jung, MBTI, Socionics, Keirsey, Social Styles, DISC, Strengths Finder and Big Five. Probably more along the way, but lets start with those.

Some key areas we explore are:

• How we see the world
• How we make decisions
• How we represent ourselves to others
• What our key strengths and weaknesses are

The group has three primary types of meetings:

I - Introduction meetings: Experienced members share their knowledge. Mainly aimed at beginners.

D - Discussion meetings: Meetings aimed at getting together and discussion or performing activities, or both

L – Lecture meetings: External guests or prominent members. These could potentially include costs for venue or presenter, or both.

Sounds good? We strive to improve continuously and hope you want to join us during our quest for knowledge.

All the best, 
Pierre, Elif, Anton, Karolina, Christopher and Parham

PS. If you haven't done any personality test yet, and would like to find out. Please take this free test to find out, and come back and join us. 

http://www.celebritytypes.com/test.php
name: Personaire - Making sense of the inside noise

description:
This is a group about self improvement through science, especially psychology, and applied math. Our ideal members are people who want to be their best selves and are willing to put in a little work to achieve that. You should be willing to do back-of-the-envelope calculations and change your mind when you receive a convincing argument.

You should join because you'll learn useful things and meet level-headed friends. You can expect talks and workshops every week or two, where one person will present material, followed by an informal discussion. Typical topics include decision theory applied to everyday life, cognitive biases to watch out for, techniques for achieving goals, and the latest research on health and nutrition. Looking forward to swapping tips and clear-headed debate with everybody!

category.name: education/learning
description:
Meet other local Philosophers, thinkers, dreamers, curious people to discuss the world and what we know about it.

Why study philosophy?

"Philosophy is to be studied, not for the sake of any definite answers to its questions, since no definite answers can, as a rule, be known to be true, but rather for the sake of the questions themselves; because these questions enlarge our conception of what is possible, enrich our intellectual imagination and diminish the dogmatic assurance which closes the mind against speculation; but above all because, through the greatness of the universe which philosophy contemplates, the mind is also rendered great, and becomes capable of that union with the universe which constitutes its highest good."

—Bertrand Russell, The Problems of Philosophy, ch. XV, The Value of Philosophy

How do we discuss and tackle philosophy?

"Recall the quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald: “The test of a first ­rate intelligence is the ability to hold two opposed ideas in the mind at the same time, and still retain the ability to function.” Do not be in a rush to say why a thinker is right or wrong; rather, be—if anything—in a rush to understand." Our goal is first and foremost to understand the great philosophers, and instead of immediately opposing the axioms they propose ("no, everything is NOT made of water"), the goal is to see where their premises may take us to.


Here are some links to topics we discuss of refer to:

www.historyofphilosophy.net/all-episodes

http://www.justiceharvard.org/

description:
What really motivates you? What makes you get up in the morning and do what you do? In this group we discuss, compare and evaluate different motivational frameworks with special focus on Reiss Motivation Profile.

The motivational research by the American Professor Steven Reiss forms the scientific basis of the Reiss Motivation Profile. Using numerous studies with thousands of trial subjects he identified a total of 16 psychological basic desires which every human being possesses. These basic desires must be satisfied in order that we feel our lives to be meaningful. They are moulded by our genes and experiences in childhood and adolescence, remain largely constant throughout our lives in accordance with previous perceptions and thus give us permanent orientation. As with every other scientific procedure in personality or motivational psychology, you have to decide entirely as an individual which indicators from the results are important or meaningful for you – and which not. The following questions may help you: How well does each basic desire characteristic describe my actual need? At which places do the statements apply particularly well, and in which points do I not recognise myself? How do I live each basic desire in my day-to-day life? These are questions that all people should be able to answer to be able to fill their lives with Value based happiness.

If you are interested in living your life (and worklife) with greater fulfillment and joy, join us in the discussion at the next meetup.

description: I love a good debate and I would argue that there are a good number of you who do so too. The idea is to create an avenue where interested parties can get together to debate one another in groups or to just sit back and listen to one. Topics can range from politics, ethics and morality, economics, legislations, rights and freedoms, or anything else that is of interest to the members. Topics that can be debated mostly on logical consistency without heavy reliance on factual accuracy will also be greatly encouraged. The goal here is not so much to win a competition but instead to become better at articulating one's ideas and in listening to and understanding each other.

description:
Nøgleordet for formålet med workshops er træning i – selvledelse.

Ved hjælp af forskellige øvelser og teknikker bliver du mere bevidst om din situation og dine muligheder, og du lærer teknikker til at gøre dine drømme til virkelighed. I privatlivet og på arbejde.

Teknikkerne hentes fra management verdenen, eksistentiel filosofi, psykoanalyse, positiv psykologi mv. 

Få inspiration til psykologiske værktøjer, som du kan bruge direkte i din dagligdag og dit personlige lederskab. Vi viser teorierne bag værktøjerne, der gør kommunikationen nemmere, og vi bruger metoderne med det samme i øvelser, så det bliver nemmere at coache og sparre med hinanden.

Formålet med møderne er at inspirere dig og pirre din nysgerrighed efter at forstå hvad, der foregår mellem og inden i os mennesker. Med viden om vores instinkter, følelser, fornuft og kroppe, så er det nemmere at få kommunikationen til at fungere.

Få svar på spørgsmål som … 

• Hvordan du skaber balance mellem fornuft og følelser?
• Hvordan du bruger dine tanker til at nå dine mål?
• Hvordan du får mere handlekraft og motivation?
• Hvordan bliver du bedre til at kommunikere i relationer?
• Hvordan kan du skabe større FLOW i dagligdagen – personligt og fagligt?
name: FLOW Lab - psykologi brugt i praksis

description:
I facilitate workshops and courses that stimulate dialogue, creative thinking and community-building through visual communication. In an increasingly disconnected society, where individualism and new technologies move people away from each other, my aim with visualagency.org ia to bring people together around the table to learn from each other, to share ideas and to develop new relationships. Collaborative drawing helps to engage with strangers, turning them into friends while engaging in discussions on important societal issues. From community and team-building to networking, Visual Agency is about stimulating curiosity, creativity and collaboration.

---------------------

Agnieszka Mlicka is a visual facilitator and founder of Visual Agency. She has a BFA Fine Art degree from the University of Oxford and an MA Painting degree from the University of the Arts London. She has undertaken 6 years of PhD research in art and architecture at Central Saint Martins, University of the Arts London. Agnieszka has a Postgraduate Certificate of Special Study in Supporting Learning (awarded with distinction), and gained teaching experience at four different universities in London and Florence.

---------------------

When RSVP'ing, please respect the Attendance and Cancellation Policy for this group, which makes it possible to have a successful event:

• It is NOT acceptable to cancel last minute. Cancellations must be done at least 2 days in advance.

• It is NOT acceptable to do a no-show. In case of a real emergency, you need to inform the organiser Agnieszka Mlicka by texting her with your name and explanation: +45 5383 4170.

• If you need to cancel, you must change your RSVP on the group's page as soon as possible, to give someone else the chance to attend.

The workshops are dependent on the energy created in small groups, so your contribution is really important for the success of these events!
name: Creative Visual Thinking Workshops

category.name: education/learning
description:
Usually the times and locations displayed for our events are wrong. The actual dates, times, and locations can be found by solving a trio of puzzles posted in the event description.



FAQ

Q - How do I find you once I reach the venue?

A - There will be a white sphinx at our table.



Q - What happens at the events?

A - There is no agenda, the events evolve into whatever participants wish to make of them. Things usually start off with drinks and conversation, further riddles and quirky ideas are frequently exchanged; after that, sometimes it’s bar hopping, sometimes we end up crashing parties at the chemistry department, sometimes we end up at somebody’s home. All options are open.



Q - I am completely and utterly stuck on one of the riddles. Any chance for an extra hint?

A - If you have given it 24h, send me a message, and I’ll be happy to provide an extra hint.



Q - I think I know the solutions for the upcoming event, but I am not sure. Would you confirm them if I sent them to you?

A - Of course. Message me, I will be happy to either confirm or give an extra hint.



Q - There is a flaw/ambiguity in one of the riddles. Should I let you know?

A - Thanks for spotting it. Yes, please do let me know.



Q - I won’t be able to join any of your events because I live far away/am agoraphobic/am serving a prison sentence/accidentally locked myself in a maintenance closet 4 years ago and can’t get out… however, I really like riddles. Can you use a beta tester?

A - Yes! Always! When making a riddle one automatically knows the solution, so gauging the difficulty is almost impossible. Beta testers are always welcome. Please send me a message.



Q - What is the purpose of this?

A - I like the idea of providing a community for people who enjoy an intellectual challenge.
name: Riddles Copenhagen

Our mission is to create a community for academics and students, who wish to build and boost a solid CV/resume while they are still at uni. We wish to bring students and graduates together, to discuss and share their success stories.

We invite all students to join, but we believe that it is academic generalists, who will benefit the most from this group. For instance, if you are a student at the Danish School of Journalism, you are much more likely to know what jobs you are looking for after graduation, than if you study at CBS, CBA, Syddansk University, AU or AAU and the like, which are more degrees that creates generalists, and not specialists. Join us in our mission to get as many students to land a job after graduation.

description:
Hello, Copenhageners!
On behalf of The Planetary Society, we are inviting you to the first Planetary Society event in Copenhagen!

Our mission is to empower the world’s citizens to advance space science and exploration. We advocate for space and planetary science funding in government, inspire and educate people around the world, and develop and fund groundbreaking space science and technology.

We introduce people to the wonders of the cosmos, bridging the gap between the scientific community and the general public to inspire and educate people from all walks of life.

We give every citizen of the planet the opportunity to make their voices heard in government and effect real change in support of space exploration.

And we bring ordinary people directly to the frontier of exploration as we crowdfund innovative and exciting space technologies.

During this event, we will introduce The Planetary Society and tell you all about its vision, mission and projects!
So if you are excited about space exploration or even want to contribute to our efforts expanding in Scandinavia, come and join us for our social evening in Studenterhuset!

category.name: education/learning
description:
There are great benefits to learning in the company others! If you’d like to supplement your solo GMAT study prep with group learning, here are some ideas we will work with in our GMAT study group:

1. Study dates
If you know a fellow student or colleague at work is also studying for the GMAT, suggest a study date, or come to the GMAT study group. This is the simplest way to enjoy the benefits of peer support. You don’t even have to be working on the same topics; having another person in the same space working toward the same goal will help to anchor you in place and keep you focused. To make a study date successful, you should define a timeframe for working individually. Schedule a break to debrief each other on what you have been doing and discuss difficulties and possible resolutions.

But remember, studying with others in the same space also requires discipline. Don’t get tempted to waste time together by talking about the latest gizmo you bought or game you played.

2. Study challenges or quests
One way to motivate yourself and your co-learners is to devise challenges for each other with a promise of a reward at the end if the challenge is successfully completed. For example, each learner can begin by mentioning a topic she/he finds difficult, and the challenge could be to correctly solve three questions of that type in under two minutes. After racking up sufficient points, you and your co-learners can reward each other with say, a movie or a dessert.

3. Synergistic learning
Often when explaining a concept out loud, we gain greater insight into our own knowledge of the concept. One way of practicing synergistic learning could be to sit together and have each participant work individually on the same question. After solving the question, compare the methods you each used. By explaining to others what you did, or seeing what others have done, you can enhance your repertoire of strategies and discover blind spots in your process.

Remember though, there may be different ways to solve a problem correctly, and not all methods are optimal for the GMAT. Compare the strategies and evaluate them for what works best in terms of effectiveness and efficiency.
name: Copenhagen GMAT study group

description:
Om Københavns Debatsamfund

Københavns Debatsamfund er stiftet for at hæve niveauet for den demokratiske samtale. Der er behov for et forum, hvor indhold og idéer kan være i højsædet, i stedet for ordstyrere og overflade.

Vi drager inspiration fra den århundredegamle engelske tradition for dannet debat.
Den disciplinerede konflikt af ideer, som en god debat kan sikre, er et af de bedste værktøjer til at opnå oplysning og sikre et levende og aktivt demokrati. Vi vil lade dem, der har noget på hjerte mødes og tale for sin sag, og opfordrer publikum til at deltage med spørgsmål, som kan belyse, hvori uenighederne består.


Den næste debat: Bør indvandringen til Danmark kraftigt begrænses?

D. 3. april kl. 16.30 på Christiansborg, står kampen mellem medlem af Europaparlamentet for Dansk Folkeparti, Morten Messerschmidt og journalist, forfatter og tidligere chefredaktør, David Trads.

Debatten omhandler et af dansk politiks mest sprængfarlige emner: Bør indvandringen til Danmark kraftigt begrænses?

Arrangement afholdes af Københavns Debatsamfund, som er stiftet for at ændre den måde den demokratiske samtale virker i Danmark ved at stille et forum til rådighed, hvor de mest markante stemmer under civiliserede former kan få frit løb for at gå i konflikt om deres idéer.

Der er plads til 140 deltagere i salen og det er gratis at deltage. Skynd dig at tilmelde dig, ved at sende en mail med dit fulde navn til kbhdebat@gmail.com.

Hvis man ønsker at reservere flere pladser, så skal man angive navnet på øvrige gæster.
name: Københavns Debatsamfund
organizer.name: Glen Stenstrup Hagensen

description:
Welcome to Socrates Café Helsinge Meetup Group!

Socrates Café Helsinge is a philosophy discussion group for the general public in which all meetups are held in Danish. Anybody is welcome to join at any time and attendance is absolutely free. Meetups will be held at the Helsinge public library every 2nd Monday within each month, from 17:00 to 18:30 within "Møderum1".

The setup for our regular meetups:

1. Welcome - remember nameplate

2. Proposal for today's topic (posed as an open question, e.g."What is freedom? How can you feel free?" )

3. The moderator will present proposals to today's issues

4. Election of today's topic - A (everyone can vote for several proposals)

5. The moderator will present the two proposals with the most votes

6. Election of today's topic - B (each can vote for their single favorite proposal)

7. Today's most voted topic is discussed (about one hour) - Marking a message by lifting his/her nameplate (moderator note the order)

8. Concluding remarks by the moderator

We aim to produce a socratic dialogue in which all participants seek to promote independent, reflective and critical thinking. It is up to each person to define what these terms mean for oneself. If participants gathers a feeling of being enriched with new thoughts for reflections about life, the goal is reached.
name: Socrates Cafe Helsinge
